title: Manitowoc Lincoln wins sectional
text:
HTR Media 7:37 p.m. CDT October 7, 2015 Tennis. 39 CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Behind sectional titles at Nos. 1, 2 and 4 singles the Manitowoc Lincoln girls tennis team took home the sectional team title Wednesday at the Kohler Sports Core. 
It was a tight finish but the host Ships edged Fox River Classic Conference foe Notre Dame by two points to add a sectional crown to their conference title. 
Bailey Budnik (No. 1) and Halimae Laurino (No. 2) both punched their tickets to Madison next week by virtue of the titles. Also victorious in singles was Isabella Ramminger. 
Rounding out the Ships singles participants was Allyson Verbauwhede, who finished second at No. 3. 
At doubles, Lincoln’s No. 1 tandem of Jen Belisle and Sydney Verbauwhede lost their first match while Dayna Decker and Julie Rohrer (No. 2) finished third. 
The top four finishers at both No. 1 singles and doubles receive automatic berths to State along with the winner of the No. 2 singles and doubles flights. 
Team State will begin Oct. 23 in Madison. 
Team results: Manitowoc Lincoln 39, Notre Dame 37, Green Bay Southwest 24, Pulaski 23, Sheboygan North 20, Kimberly 18, De Pere 18, West De Pere 15, Bay Port 9, Sheboygan South 6, Ashwaubenon 4, Antigo 2, Green Bay Preble 2 
Division 2 
Brown Deer sectional: For a fourth consecutive season Roncalli’s Tallie Piaskowski will be headed to the state tournament in Madison. 
Piaskowski won the No. 1 singles flight at Brown Deer and will look to claim a state crown after finishing second last season. 
Joining her at State will be teammates and the Jets’ No. 1 doubles tandem Abby Welnetz and Maddie Salutz, who took third. 
Julia Platteter finished second at No. 2 singles as did Reese Wetenkamp at No. 4. 
Also from the area was Two Rivers, which was represented by their No. 1 doubles duo of Gabby Weier and Megan Sosnosky. The pair lost their first match.
